                <h1>How Many Otters Are There Worldwide?</h1>
                <p>Estimating the exact number of otters in the world is challenging due to their diverse habitats and elusive nature. There are 13 species of otters, and populations vary greatly. While some species, like the North American river otter, are relatively abundant, others, like the sea otter, face endangerment due to habitat loss and pollution. Conservation efforts continue to help monitor and protect these playful creatures.</p>
